msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "YunoHost can be installed \"on top\" of Debian. This can be useful if you already have a Debian machine or can't use the recommended methods. Note that there is no actual difference in your resulting YunoHost installation between doing this and using the other methods involving pre-installed images: the pre-installed images are just convenient to skip a bunch of steps and having the system already shipped with everything needed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "<FAIcon icon=\"fa-download\" /> Get Debian"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "You should download the version **Bookworm** (Debian 12) and select the architecture for your PC. When in doubt, select `amd64`, or `i386` for a pre-2010 PC.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "  <Button url=\"https://www.debian.org/distrib/netinst\" color=\"skyblue\"><SmallInline url=\"/img/icons/logo-debian.png\" alt=\"Debian logo\"/> Debian Download page</Button>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternatively, you can browse the [Debian archive](https://cdimage.debian.org/mirror/cdimage/archive) for the latest 12.x version, select your architecture, the select `iso-cd` and download the `netinst` iso.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "You might want to **wipe the hard drive** before starting the Debian installer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "Flash the ISO your USB key, for example using [Etcher](https://www.balena.io/etcher/), [USBimager](https://bztsrc.gitlab.io/usbimager/) or `dd`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Debian installer will ask for a **hostname** and a **domain name**. You can use `yunohost` and `yunohost.local`. It is not that important since the YunoHost Installer will overwrite those anyway.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Debian will ask for a **root password**, which should be reaonably complex as it is your primary defense to possible attacks.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "The installer will also ask for a **user account** and another password.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced div block (warning)
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "**IMPORTANT:** this username should be DIFFERENT from the first YunoHost user which you will choose during YunoHost's posinstallâ€¦ For example, you can name it `debian`. Be sure to also use a long complex password.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "When the install asks where to install and how to **create disk partitions**, select the option to **use the whole disk**, unless you know what you're doing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- We recommend not to separate the `/home`, `/var` or `/tmp` partitions. Use the option to \"keep all files in one partition\".\n"
"- If you don't know what you're doing, don't encrypt the disk (Decryption at power-on will be an issue)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "The installer will ask about **mirrors**. Select a country and server close to your location, or use the default options.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "The installer will ask which **desktop environment** you want. This is generally useless and might waste resources.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- Unselect all desktop environment\n"
"- Keep \"standard system utilities\" checked\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "After installing Debian"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/admin/05.get_started/20.install_on/on_top_of_debian.mdx:59
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1. Remove the installation media (unplug the USB stick)\n"
"2. Reboot\n"
"3. Login as `root`\n"
"4. Install curl by typing `apt install curl`\n"
msgstr ""
